            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Followup on this: \n\n`SourcePre` and `SourcePost` are intended to serve the purpose of handling plugin loading, but they currently don't handle plugins that lack a `plugin/foo.lua` file ([opencode.nvim](https://github.com/NickvanDyke/opencode.nvim/) is an example).\n\nRelated:\n- https://github.com/vim/vim/issues/3739\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/9415\n\nPotential solutions:\n- fire `SourcePre` for more cases, e.g. `:packadd foo` emits `SourcePre foo` regardless of the actual plugin source\n- strongly encourage all plugins to provide a `plugin/foo.lua` file: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/35854\n- introduce `PackAdd` event\n- ...?\n\ncc @echasnovski ",
